{
    "publish_date": "2010-07-13T08:21:40.000Z", 
    "video_length": "PT19M48S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "I feel really privileged to be here.", 
            "dur": "4.333", 
            "start": "12.217"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I have cried, I have laughed,", 
            "dur": "3.578", 
            "start": "16.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I have been profoundly touched", 
            "dur": "5.29", 
            "start": "20.128"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and I feel really privileged to be alive.", 
            "dur": "4.241", 
            "start": "25.418"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I am grateful that I am alive.", 
            "dur": "4.19", 
            "start": "29.659"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In 1944, my parents were in a concentration camp", 
            "dur": "4.089", 
            "start": "33.849"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in Vichy, France.", 
            "dur": "3.781", 
            "start": "37.938"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "My mother engineered an escape.", 
            "dur": "4.511", 
            "start": "41.719"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "She actually got my father out.", 
            "dur": "4.193", 
            "start": "46.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And my parents walked through the Alps.", 
            "dur": "5.678", 
            "start": "50.423"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "My mother was pregnant with me.", 
            "dur": "3.68", 
            "start": "56.101"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And when they got to the Swiss border,", 
            "dur": "2.653", 
            "start": "59.781"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the border was closed to refugees.", 
            "dur": "4.717", 
            "start": "62.434"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "My mother threw herself into Switzerland.", 
            "dur": "4.49", 
            "start": "67.151"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Anything for her was better than going back", 
            "dur": "4.183", 
            "start": "71.641"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to the hell she came from.", 
            "dur": "3.76", 
            "start": "75.824"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And my father succeeded in smuggling \nhimself a few days later.", 
            "dur": "7.996", 
            "start": "79.584"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And in 1944, I was born.", 
            "dur": "7.277", 
            "start": "87.58"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Decades later I am sitting with my mother", 
            "dur": "2.962", 
            "start": "94.857"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in an old age home in Israel.", 
            "dur": "3.998", 
            "start": "97.819"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I cannot bear to see her.", 
            "dur": "4.565", 
            "start": "101.817"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "(fights, tears, sighs)", 
            "dur": "5.52", 
            "start": "106.382"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "She is sitting in a wheel-chair.", 
            "dur": "2.918", 
            "start": "111.902"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "She doesn&#39;t know who I am.", 
            "dur": "4.082", 
            "start": "114.82"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I feel guilty. I feel sad. I am struggling. I am angry.", 
            "dur": "6.586", 
            "start": "118.902"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is my hero. Why should she be here?", 
            "dur": "6.015", 
            "start": "125.488"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I realize that I am not visiting her.", 
            "dur": "5.397", 
            "start": "131.503"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I am with my own emotions.", 
            "dur": "2.324", 
            "start": "136.9"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I make a decision.", 
            "dur": "3.516", 
            "start": "139.224"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I am going to cross the bridge", 
            "dur": "2.921", 
            "start": "142.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to the world of my mother.", 
            "dur": "1.765", 
            "start": "145.661"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I will leave the world where I am struggling.", 
            "dur": "5.473", 
            "start": "147.426"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I and will go and meet her.", 
            "dur": "2.441", 
            "start": "152.899"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I will bring with me new eyes.", 
            "dur": "4.922", 
            "start": "155.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And so I did. I came, I sat across from her \nand I crossed the bridge.", 
            "dur": "8.07", 
            "start": "160.262"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I landed in her world. And I looked at her.", 
            "dur": "6.053", 
            "start": "168.332"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And she looked at me.", 
            "dur": "2.675", 
            "start": "174.385"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And in Yiddish she said:", 
            "dur": "4.807", 
            "start": "177.06"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Du bist mein Tochter.&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.558", 
            "start": "181.867"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You are my daughter.", 
            "dur": "3.297", 
            "start": "184.425"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I started to cry and with her hands \nshe gently wiped my tears.", 
            "dur": "9.586", 
            "start": "187.722"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "She hadn&#39;t recognized me for months.", 
            "dur": "3.352", 
            "start": "197.308"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Of course, I hadn&#39;t been there - emotionally.", 
            "dur": "9.321", 
            "start": "200.66"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This miracle with my mother illustrates", 
            "dur": "3.273", 
            "start": "209.981"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the three invisible connectors \nthat I want to talk to you about today.", 
            "dur": "6.847", 
            "start": "213.254"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It is the relational space - the space.", 
            "dur": "4.123", 
            "start": "220.101"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It is the bridge between the worlds - the bridge.", 
            "dur": "4.681", 
            "start": "224.224"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And it is the encounter.", 
            "dur": "2.913", 
            "start": "228.905"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Human essence to human essence. The encounter.", 
            "dur": "8.067", 
            "start": "231.818"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "These three invisible connectors - you know them.", 
            "dur": "7.176", 
            "start": "239.885"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You live them.", 
            "dur": "1.809", 
            "start": "247.061"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But you may never have framed them that way.", 
            "dur": "3.681", 
            "start": "248.87"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And in working with couples for many, many years", 
            "dur": "3.077", 
            "start": "252.551"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I have come to see that those are \nthe three invisible connectors.", 
            "dur": "8.534", 
            "start": "255.628"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let me start by talking to you about the space.", 
            "dur": "3.714", 
            "start": "264.162"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It is the Jewish philosopher Martin Buber who said:", 
            "dur": "6.025", 
            "start": "267.876"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Our relationship lives in the space between us.&quot;", 
            "dur": "7.199", 
            "start": "273.901"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It doesn&#39;t live in me or in you", 
            "dur": "3.961", 
            "start": "281.1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or even in the dialogue between the two of us.", 
            "dur": "5.839", 
            "start": "285.061"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It lives in the space that we live together.", 
            "dur": "6.086", 
            "start": "290.9"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And he said: &quot;That space is sacred space.&quot;", 
            "dur": "6.955", 
            "start": "296.986"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, if we don&#39;t know about the space,", 
            "dur": "3.763", 
            "start": "303.941"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "if we don&#39;t know how to take responsibility", 
            "dur": "3.27", 
            "start": "307.704"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "for the space we live together,", 
            "dur": "2.966", 
            "start": "310.974"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we will actually pollute it", 
            "dur": "3.246", 
            "start": "313.94"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the way I polluted the space with my mother.", 
            "dur": "2.719", 
            "start": "317.186"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I polluted the space with my mother", 
            "dur": "1.955", 
            "start": "319.905"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "not because I was feeling my feelings.", 
            "dur": "3.314", 
            "start": "321.86"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I polluted the space with my mother", 
            "dur": "2.037", 
            "start": "325.174"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "because I unconsciously put all these \nemotions in the middle between us", 
            "dur": "6.759", 
            "start": "327.211"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "- unconsciously.", 
            "dur": "2.972", 
            "start": "333.97"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "When we don&#39;t know about the space,", 
            "dur": "3.998", 
            "start": "336.942"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we pollute it quite automatically.", 
            "dur": "4.002", 
            "start": "340.94"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "A word, a look, a reaction, a withdrawal,", 
            "dur": "6.201", 
            "start": "344.942"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a criticism, a judgement.", 
            "dur": "1.959", 
            "start": "351.143"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We put it there, unconsciously.", 
            "dur": "4.283", 
            "start": "353.102"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And the space becomes uncomfortable.", 
            "dur": "4.64", 
            "start": "357.385"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And when the space is uncomfortable,", 
            "dur": "1.957", 
            "start": "362.025"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we react to the discomfort in the space", 
            "dur": "2.783", 
            "start": "363.982"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and the space becomes more uncomfortable.", 
            "dur": "3.738", 
            "start": "366.765"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And slowly but surely, discomfort after \ndiscomfort, the space becomes dangerous.", 
            "dur": "7.68", 
            "start": "370.503"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And then we react to the danger in the space.", 
            "dur": "4.918", 
            "start": "378.183"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And how do we react?", 
            "dur": "2.527", 
            "start": "383.101"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Some of us react by exploding our energy.", 
            "dur": "3.52", 
            "start": "385.628"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We talk louder, we shout, we say many words,", 
            "dur": "3.514", 
            "start": "389.148"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we are in your face.", 
            "dur": "2.522", 
            "start": "392.662"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Some of us react to the danger in the space", 
            "dur": "4.192", 
            "start": "395.184"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "by constricting, hiding, withdrawing our energy.", 
            "dur": "5.936", 
            "start": "399.376"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And once those two reactions come together", 
            "dur": "3.265", 
            "start": "405.312"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as a reaction to the danger in the space,", 
            "dur": "2.563", 
            "start": "408.577"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the danger grows", 
            "dur": "1.76", 
            "start": "411.14"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and now we are reacting together \nto the pollution and danger", 
            "dur": "5.001", 
            "start": "412.9"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we co-created in the relational space.", 
            "dur": "5.601", 
            "start": "417.901"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What shall we do?", 
            "dur": "1.398", 
            "start": "423.502"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "How do we take responsibility for the space between us?", 
            "dur": "6.362", 
            "start": "424.9"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Which is sacred, as says Martin Buber.", 
            "dur": "3.962", 
            "start": "431.262"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Here comes the metaphor of the bridge.", 
            "dur": "2.872", 
            "start": "435.224"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We take responsibility for the space between us", 
            "dur": "4.044", 
            "start": "438.096"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "by crossing the bridge to the world of the other", 
            "dur": "4.44", 
            "start": "442.14"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and bringing our full presence on the other side.", 
            "dur": "6.725", 
            "start": "446.58"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "How do we do it?", 
            "dur": "2.597", 
            "start": "453.305"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "First, sit down.", 
            "dur": "4.359", 
            "start": "455.902"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Take a deep breath.", 
            "dur": "2.259", 
            "start": "460.261"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Put your feet on the ground.", 
            "dur": "4.21", 
            "start": "462.52"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Allow yourself to get to the present moment.", 
            "dur": "4.372", 
            "start": "466.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Align yourself with here and now.", 
            "dur": "5.319", 
            "start": "471.102"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Know that you are alive! Be grateful", 
            "dur": "4.885", 
            "start": "476.421"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "for this moment of your life. Right now!", 
            "dur": "5.758", 
            "start": "481.306"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That already is a very important beginning", 
            "dur": "4.967", 
            "start": "487.064"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "for your journey across the bridge.", 
            "dur": "2.459", 
            "start": "492.031"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And then, you begin to consciously and deliberately", 
            "dur": "5.695", 
            "start": "494.49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "walk the bridge -- slipping the rubber band", 
            "dur": "5.214", 
            "start": "500.185"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that pulls you back to your prejudices, \nyour story, your identity,", 
            "dur": "4.423", 
            "start": "505.399"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "who you think you are, your feelings, \nyour emotions, whatever it is in your world.", 
            "dur": "6.704", 
            "start": "509.822"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "All you take with you across the bridge", 
            "dur": "3.346", 
            "start": "516.526"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is a little plastic bag, transparent,", 
            "dur": "3.553", 
            "start": "519.872"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "with a passport and a visa.", 
            "dur": "3.077", 
            "start": "523.425"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The reason it needs to be transparent:", 
            "dur": "1.998", 
            "start": "526.502"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you cannot bring anything of yours \nto the other side of the bridge.", 
            "dur": "6.13", 
            "start": "528.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And when you have landed", 
            "dur": "1.95", 
            "start": "534.63"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "on the other side, what do you do?", 
            "dur": "4.059", 
            "start": "536.58"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You listen.", 
            "dur": "2.38", 
            "start": "540.639"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You listen with an open heart.", 
            "dur": "4.678", 
            "start": "543.019"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You listen with new eyes.", 
            "dur": "4.031", 
            "start": "547.697"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It is Marcel Proust, the French writer, who said:", 
            "dur": "3.757", 
            "start": "551.728"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;The adventure of life is not about \ndiscovering new landscape.", 
            "dur": "6.217", 
            "start": "555.485"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The adventure of life is \nseeing the old ones with new eyes.&quot;", 
            "dur": "5.77", 
            "start": "561.702"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And you bring your new eyes and your open heart", 
            "dur": "2.869", 
            "start": "567.472"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and your generosity of spirit", 
            "dur": "1.61", 
            "start": "570.341"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and you listen as if you&#39;re \nlearning a new language,", 
            "dur": "5.052", 
            "start": "571.966"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a new music, a new rhythm.", 
            "dur": "3.719", 
            "start": "577.018"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You listen by repeating the words.", 
            "dur": "4.123", 
            "start": "580.737"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I hear you say.", 
            "dur": "3.721", 
            "start": "584.86"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Have I got you?&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.815", 
            "start": "588.581"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And you learn. You learn about \nthe landscape in this other world.", 
            "dur": "9.33", 
            "start": "591.396"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And so what can happen on the other side?", 
            "dur": "4.019", 
            "start": "600.726"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And what happens on the other side", 
            "dur": "2.355", 
            "start": "604.745"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is the encounter.", 
            "dur": "2.485", 
            "start": "607.1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, what is the encounter?", 
            "dur": "3.735", 
            "start": "609.585"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "On a biological level, the encounter", 
            "dur": "3.181", 
            "start": "613.32"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is the resonance between two brains.", 
            "dur": "3.498", 
            "start": "616.501"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The relational neurobiologists \ncall this resonance the brain bridge.", 
            "dur": "6.203", 
            "start": "619.999"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Two limbic systems that resonate together.", 
            "dur": "4.623", 
            "start": "626.202"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The seed of our emotions \nbeginning to resonate together.", 
            "dur": "5.835", 
            "start": "630.825"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And relational neurobiologists have found that", 
            "dur": "3.569", 
            "start": "636.66"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "when there is this resonance between two brains,", 
            "dur": "3.511", 
            "start": "640.229"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "our central nervous system begins to calm down.", 
            "dur": "5.335", 
            "start": "643.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Because, they have also discovered,", 
            "dur": "2.914", 
            "start": "649.075"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that our brain is the only organ inside of us", 
            "dur": "5.591", 
            "start": "651.989"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that doesn&#39;t regulate from within.", 
            "dur": "2.92", 
            "start": "657.58"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It regulates on the outside \nthrough another brain.", 
            "dur": "7.241", 
            "start": "660.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We need each other for self-regulation.", 
            "dur": "3.955", 
            "start": "667.741"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We can only regulate through the other.", 
            "dur": "3.645", 
            "start": "671.696"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Through the eyes of the other. \nThrough that resonance.", 
            "dur": "4.441", 
            "start": "675.341"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And what happens then is very interesting", 
            "dur": "2.921", 
            "start": "679.782"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "because, 10 years ago approximately, \nrelational neurobiologists", 
            "dur": "4.402", 
            "start": "682.703"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "discovered those mirror neurons", 
            "dur": "2.984", 
            "start": "687.105"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that we have in our brain.", 
            "dur": "1.853", 
            "start": "690.089"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Our capacity for compassion,", 
            "dur": "3.748", 
            "start": "691.942"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "for empathy,", 
            "dur": "1.819", 
            "start": "695.69"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "for deep, deep understanding of the other.", 
            "dur": "4.906", 
            "start": "697.509"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And during the encounter these \nmirror neurons become very alive.", 
            "dur": "5.586", 
            "start": "702.415"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And what happens then?", 
            "dur": "2.019", 
            "start": "708.001"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "New neural pathways begin to form in the brain.", 
            "dur": "4.8", 
            "start": "710.02"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "New neural pathways that give us", 
            "dur": "3.285", 
            "start": "714.82"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the capacity to be in relationship.", 
            "dur": "3.637", 
            "start": "718.105"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Because the brain has been found \nto have an enormous plasticity.", 
            "dur": "4.928", 
            "start": "721.742"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It can change at any time during our lifetime.", 
            "dur": "5.115", 
            "start": "726.67"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And so these new neuro-pathways \nthat are formed in our brain", 
            "dur": "4.197", 
            "start": "731.785"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "give us a chance to become", 
            "dur": "2.124", 
            "start": "735.982"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "more relationally intelligent", 
            "dur": "3.076", 
            "start": "738.106"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and more relationally mature.", 
            "dur": "4.998", 
            "start": "741.182"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, that is the encounter in the biological sense.", 
            "dur": "7.732", 
            "start": "746.18"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But in another domain it is harder to define", 
            "dur": "5.03", 
            "start": "753.912"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "what the encounter is.", 
            "dur": "2.638", 
            "start": "758.942"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It is the meeting of two full human presences.", 
            "dur": "6.92", 
            "start": "761.58"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Or two human essences. \nOr the life force in each person.", 
            "dur": "6.492", 
            "start": "768.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Or the meeting of two souls.", 
            "dur": "3.832", 
            "start": "774.992"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And what is that life force?", 
            "dur": "2.118", 
            "start": "778.824"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What is the human essence?", 
            "dur": "4.149", 
            "start": "780.942"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "My father has a story about that.", 
            "dur": "2.38", 
            "start": "785.091"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "My father had the largest collection of \nYiddish stories in the universe.", 
            "dur": "6.19", 
            "start": "787.471"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And he loved to tell them.", 
            "dur": "2.599", 
            "start": "793.661"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And he laughed harder than anyone", 
            "dur": "2.44", 
            "start": "796.26"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "when he told his stories.", 
            "dur": "3.715", 
            "start": "798.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This story is about Mr. Goldberg, the tailor.", 
            "dur": "5.181", 
            "start": "802.415"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So somebody came to get a suit \nfrom Mr. Goldberg, the tailor.", 
            "dur": "5.186", 
            "start": "807.596"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And he tries on the suit and he says:", 
            "dur": "2.079", 
            "start": "812.782"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Mr. Goldberg, this suit looks very strange.", 
            "dur": "2.4", 
            "start": "814.861"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This sleeve doesn&#39;t fit at all.&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.17", 
            "start": "817.261"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And Mr. Goldberg looks very seriously and he says:", 
            "dur": "2.7", 
            "start": "819.431"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;You are right. For that sleeve you \nhave to hold your hand like that. OK?&quot;", 
            "dur": "7.015", 
            "start": "822.131"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The man says: &quot;You know, \nthe other sleeve doesn&#39;t fit at all.&quot;", 
            "dur": "3.634", 
            "start": "829.146"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Look, look at it!&quot; - Mr. Goldberg says:", 
            "dur": "2.508", 
            "start": "832.78"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;You are completely right. For that \nsleeve you hold your hand like that", 
            "dur": "4.786", 
            "start": "835.288"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and you put this shoulder like this. OK?&quot;", 
            "dur": "3.974", 
            "start": "840.074"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;What about the right leg? The right leg \nlooks very strange. What about it?&quot;", 
            "dur": "6.732", 
            "start": "844.048"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And Mr. Goldberg says: &quot;You are right. \nYou just have to put your foot", 
            "dur": "3.08", 
            "start": "850.78"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a little bit inside like that.&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.748", 
            "start": "853.86"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;What about this one?&quot;, he says.\n&quot;Well, that one you put your foot like this.&quot;", 
            "dur": "4.438", 
            "start": "856.608"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, now the suit was fine and \nthe man comes out of the tailor store", 
            "dur": "4.978", 
            "start": "861.046"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and as he is walking in the street \nthis couple comes by", 
            "dur": "3.721", 
            "start": "866.024"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and the woman says to her husband: \n&quot;What an amazing tailor!", 
            "dur": "3.916", 
            "start": "869.745"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "A man in this condition - the suit fits him perfectly!&quot;", 
            "dur": "6.117", 
            "start": "873.661"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "(Applause)", 
            "dur": "2.642", 
            "start": "879.778"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well... This is us. We are in this suit.", 
            "dur": "5.865", 
            "start": "882.42"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We walk around in this suit \nbecause we have adapted to our life.", 
            "dur": "5.018", 
            "start": "888.285"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And we don&#39;t even know that \nthis is a suit, a survival suit.", 
            "dur": "4.569", 
            "start": "893.303"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We know that this is us.", 
            "dur": "2.991", 
            "start": "897.872"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "For example, if I adapted by being \nwithdrawn and cold and really distant,", 
            "dur": "6.839", 
            "start": "900.863"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I think this is me.", 
            "dur": "2.207", 
            "start": "907.702"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Inside the suit is our human essence - intact!", 
            "dur": "6.427", 
            "start": "909.909"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Inside of our survival adaptation \nwe are our essence.", 
            "dur": "7.966", 
            "start": "916.337"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And coming over the bridge \nallows our spirit to be nourished.", 
            "dur": "6.358", 
            "start": "924.303"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And this transformation to happen \nfrom this survival suit", 
            "dur": "5.536", 
            "start": "930.661"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to our true human essence.", 
            "dur": "3.388", 
            "start": "936.197"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It is in being with each other \nthat our essence becomes revealed.", 
            "dur": "6.78", 
            "start": "939.585"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It so it reminds me of this wonderful saying:", 
            "dur": "3.736", 
            "start": "946.365"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;I used to be different. \nAnd now I am the same.&quot;", 
            "dur": "7.565", 
            "start": "950.101"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I started with a story about my mother.", 
            "dur": "3.237", 
            "start": "957.666"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;d like to tell you one now \nabout my grandson Leo.", 
            "dur": "4.961", 
            "start": "960.903"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I was in Istanbul with Leo. \nAnd we were in bed", 
            "dur": "5.54", 
            "start": "965.864"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "snuggling and watching a movie.", 
            "dur": "4.349", 
            "start": "971.404"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And at the end of the movie\nLeo looked at me", 
            "dur": "2.428", 
            "start": "975.753"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and he said:", 
            "dur": "2.238", 
            "start": "978.181"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Bube, grandma, I love you.&quot;", 
            "dur": "4.629", 
            "start": "980.419"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I said: &quot;I love you, too, Leo.&quot;", 
            "dur": "4.853", 
            "start": "985.048"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And he said: &quot;No. I love you.&quot;", 
            "dur": "5.197", 
            "start": "989.901"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I said: &quot;Sure, sweety, \nyou love me and I love you.&quot;", 
            "dur": "6.201", 
            "start": "995.098"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He said: &quot;No, Bube. I love you.&quot;", 
            "dur": "5.309", 
            "start": "1001.299"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And then I understood.", 
            "dur": "2.461", 
            "start": "1006.608"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He didn&#39;t want me to deflect his love.", 
            "dur": "3.15", 
            "start": "1009.069"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He wanted me to step over the bridge to come to him", 
            "dur": "4.01", 
            "start": "1012.219"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to take in the pure, \nessential love he was giving me.", 
            "dur": "7.877", 
            "start": "1016.229"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And so I did. I looked at him. I took him in.", 
            "dur": "5.076", 
            "start": "1024.106"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I let what he was giving me \nin that moment penetrate.", 
            "dur": "5.333", 
            "start": "1029.182"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I said: &quot;Leo, I hear you say: You love me.&quot;", 
            "dur": "5.269", 
            "start": "1034.515"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And his face just shone.", 
            "dur": "4.056", 
            "start": "1039.784"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He was teaching me that \nit takes courage to be connected.", 
            "dur": "7.95", 
            "start": "1043.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;d like to share with you \none of my favourite quotes", 
            "dur": "4.465", 
            "start": "1051.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "by the Sufi poet Rumi, of the 13th century,", 
            "dur": "5.046", 
            "start": "1056.255"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "who said: &quot;Beyond right thinking", 
            "dur": "5.56", 
            "start": "1061.301"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and beyond wrong thinking", 
            "dur": "3.041", 
            "start": "1066.861"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "there is a field.", 
            "dur": "2.64", 
            "start": "1069.902"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I will meet you there.&quot;", 
            "dur": "3.728", 
            "start": "1072.542"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I have a dream. \nI envision 90 million couples", 
            "dur": "5.58", 
            "start": "1076.27"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "honoring the three invisible connectors,", 
            "dur": "3.812", 
            "start": "1081.85"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "honoring the space between them, \ncrossing the bridge to each other", 
            "dur": "4.24", 
            "start": "1085.662"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and encountering each other, \nhuman essence to human essence.", 
            "dur": "3.879", 
            "start": "1089.902"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It is enormously important to me\nbecause our children grow", 
            "dur": "4.757", 
            "start": "1093.781"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in the space between us.", 
            "dur": "3.725", 
            "start": "1098.538"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The space between the couple", 
            "dur": "2.604", 
            "start": "1102.263"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is the playground of the child.", 
            "dur": "3.036", 
            "start": "1104.867"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And when we know how to honor that space", 
            "dur": "2.876", 
            "start": "1107.903"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and make it sacred, our children can blossom", 
            "dur": "3.23", 
            "start": "1110.779"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in sacred space.", 
            "dur": "2.329", 
            "start": "1114.009"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I have a date in mind. \nNovember 11th, 2012.", 
            "dur": "7.323", 
            "start": "1116.338"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "International Crossing The Bridge Day.", 
            "dur": "5.792", 
            "start": "1123.661"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It isn&#39;t just for couples.", 
            "dur": "3.091", 
            "start": "1129.453"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It is for human beings \nand it is for nations.", 
            "dur": "4.232", 
            "start": "1132.544"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I envision a time when nations", 
            "dur": "3.815", 
            "start": "1136.776"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "will know that the space between them", 
            "dur": "4.401", 
            "start": "1140.591"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is sacred space. \nThat there is a bridge", 
            "dur": "3.247", 
            "start": "1144.992"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to cross to know the culture of the other.", 
            "dur": "4.045", 
            "start": "1148.239"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And that we can encounter each other.", 
            "dur": "3.446", 
            "start": "1152.284"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Human essence to human essence.", 
            "dur": "5.612", 
            "start": "1155.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Beyond right thinking \nand beyond wrong thinking", 
            "dur": "5.166", 
            "start": "1161.342"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "there is a field.", 
            "dur": "2.394", 
            "start": "1166.508"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I will you meet you there.", 
            "dur": "3.707", 
            "start": "1168.902"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Thank you.", 
            "dur": "1.926", 
            "start": "1172.609"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "(Applause)", 
            "dur": "7.371", 
            "start": "1174.535"
        }
    ], 
